OL,3,CCall for Guernsey officers to receive
OL,4,Cmore training in charging abuse
OL,5,Csuspects
OL,7,FIt highlighted the need for a training
OL,8,Fplan around police custody sergeant
OL,9,Fprocesses and decision-making.
OL,11,FIn the UK, people cannot be charged
OL,12,Fwith domestic abuse without the input
OL,13,Fof a Crown Prosecution Lawyer.
OL,15,FHowever, this is not the case in
OL,16,FGuernsey, and the inspector who wrote
OL,17,Fthe letter refers to a culture of "if
OL,18,Fin doubt, charge, and let the courts
OL,19,Fdecide", which can lead to domestic
OL,20,Fabuse cases being dropped by the
OL,21,Fcourts.
