OL,3,CCall for Guernsey officers to receive
OL,4,Cmore training in charging abuse
OL,5,Csuspects
OL,7,FIn a statement on Monday 21 October,
OL,8,FDeputy Chief Officer Richard Bell
OL,9,Fsays: "The email in question relates
OL,10,Fto our approach to domestic abuse and
OL,11,Fquite rightly identifies areas for
OL,12,Fimprovement.
OL,14,F"Guernsey Police is determined to do
OL,15,Fall it can to address domestic abuse
OL,16,Fwhenever it occurs.
OL,18,F"We will work tirelessly to improve
OL,19,Fthe support we provide to victims in
OL,20,Fthe relentless pursuit of offenders."
