OL,4,Cmore training in charging abuse
OL,5,Csuspects
OL,7,F"It highlighted the vulnerable nature
OL,8,Fof victims and the coercive and
OL,9,Fcontrolling behaviour of offenders,
OL,10,Fproviding officers and partners with
OL,11,Fthe opportunity to work through real-
OL,12,Flife incidents.
OL,14,F"In anticipation of the new
OL,15,Flegislation, I have already
OL,16,Fcommissioned a review of our training
OL,17,Fneeds to ensure our officers and staff
OL,18,Fare equipped and supported to use the
OL,19,Fnew powers."
