OL,5,Csuspects
OL,7,FSafer says that while they cannot
OL,8,Fcomment specifically on police
OL,9,Ftraining, but says that there is a
OL,10,Fcurrent lack of legislation that
OL,11,Faffords domestic abuse victims any
OL,12,Fprotection while an investigation
OL,13,Ftakes place.
OL,15,FThey state: "Without this current
OL,16,Fprotection through legislation, a
OL,17,Fvictim who makes a complaint is left
OL,18,Fopen to further risk of harm by the
OL,19,Fperpetrator of the reported offence.
